The paper proposes a novel spatio-temporal predictive model for opioid overdose forecasting using deep learning architecture. The model incorporates multi-head attentional networks and community-attentive networks to learn different representation subspaces of features. The paper also focuses on real-time crime dynamics and their links with opioid use and criminal activities. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
